name: Slow Cooker White Chicken Chili
author: Pam Cooking Spray
summary: A slow cooker recipe for white chicken chili assembled quickly with chicken thighs, canned beans and zesty tomatoes.
ingredients: 1  serving PAM® Original No-Stick Cooking Spray
2 (15 ounce) cans Great Northern beans, undrained
1 (10 ounce) can RO*TEL Diced Tomatoes and Green Chilies, undrained
directions: Spray inside of 4-quart slow cooker with cooking spray
Place 1 can of beans in slow cooker; mash with potato masher or spoon until smooth
Add second can of beans and all remaining ingredients to slow cooker; stir to combine
Cover; cook on LOW 8 hours or on HIGH 4 hours
Carefully separate chicken into bite-size pieces
